      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Failure Modes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Speaker leakage."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The output sounds more like the model's average voice than the target. Cause: reference too short (<3 s) or too noisy; the embedding failed to capture identity. Fix: longer, cleaner reference; multiple clips."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Accent drift."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The synthesised output drops the target speaker's accent. Common in models trained predominantly on standard American English when cloning non-native speakers."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Hallucination / repetition."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Autoregressive codec LMs (GPT-based) can loop tokens or skip words. Mitigation: repetition penalty, temperature tuning, sentence-by-sentence synthesis."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Prosody mismatch."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The model copies the prosodic style of the reference (e.g., question intonation on a statement). Fix: use reference clips with neutral, conversational delivery; avoid reference clips with strong emotion."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Few-shot cloning requires only 3–30 s of reference audio and no retraining; a speaker encoder converts the reference to an embedding that conditions the TTS decoder."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "XTTS v2 is the best open-source option: 17 languages, works from 3 s, RTF < 0.3 on GPU, with a streaming API."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Tortoise TTS achieves higher MOS scores but is 10–50x slower; suitable when quality matters more than speed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "VALL-E treats cloning as in-context language modelling over codec tokens — no explicit speaker encoder; the reference audio tokens are the prompt."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reference audio quality dominates output quality: clean, single-speaker, high-SNR clips of 10–30 s produce the best results. Denoising and silence trimming are cheap wins."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Measure cloning quality with SECS (speaker cosine similarity, target >0.85) and CER (intelligibility, target <5%) alongside human MOS ratings."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fine-tuning remains superior when you need >0.90 SECS and have access to 30+ minutes of clean target-speaker audio."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
